6.20	Robert_Thom	Robert Thom	Robert Thom (March 4, 1915 in Grand Rapids, Michigan - December 31, 1979 in Alma, Michigan) was an American illustrator who specialized in the portrayal of historical scenes for commercial patrons. He is perhaps best known for his series of 40 paintings depicting the history of pharmacy, and his series of 45 paintings depicting the history of medicine, both commissioned by Parke-Davis.	
